getVariableName

public java.lang.String getVariableName(Fact fact)
Return a variable name for a fact type. The name is cached in a map, so any subsequent call with the same fact type will return the same variable. If the fact type is requested for the first time, a new variable name will be generated with the form var with an incrementing index starting at 0 ( ex : var0, var1, var2 )

Parameters:
fact - fact to request a variable for
Returns:
variable name matching the fact type

extractVariable

public ObrUpdateContext.ExtractVariableResult extractVariable(Expression expression)
'variable-ify' an expression : ex : FullfillLineVo.ShippingInstructions -> var0.ShippingInstructions. See ExtractVariableResult class above Subsequent calls to this method will return the same variable for the same fact type . different fact type will generate a new variable name: ex : FullfillLineVo.ShippingInstructions -> var0.ShippingInstructions ResponseRL.groupType -> var1.groupType FullfillLineVo.CategoryCode -> var0.CategoryCode

Parameters:
expression - expression to extract a variable from ( ex: "FullfillLineVo.ShippingInstructions" )
Returns:
extracted information from the expression. null if the expression is null, empty, or does not contain a '.'
